<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-12917] Increase error margin in SplitterTest</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-12917</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;SplitterTest is a randomized test - it generates random tokens and splits the ranges in equal parts. Since it is random we sometimes get very big vnodes right where we want a split and that makes the split unbalanced&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Bumping the error margin a bit will avoid these false positives.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
